Never before has the world seen

472
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:44,625
such a perfect couple.

473
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:46,416
[TSUTSUI, REO]
Come, leap into my arms!

474
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,791
It's hug time! Yeah!

475
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:50,625
[KASUMI]
However, the House of Montague

476
00:18:50,708 --> 00:18:52,875
and the House of Capulet
were locked in a feud,

477
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:54,250
because fate is cruel like that.

478
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:56,291
[KAWAFUJI] Huh. I thought
Handa would be the lead.

479
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:58,333
[KASUMI] Still, the flame
of passion that burned

480
00:18:58,416 --> 00:19:00,666
between the lovers could
not be extinguished.

481
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:03,666
Let's break this shiz down, yo!

482
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:12,833
[STUDENTS] O Romeo, Romeo!
Wherefore art thou Romeo?

483
00:19:12,916 --> 00:19:15,125
You know how it goes!

484
00:19:15,208 --> 00:19:17,333
[KAWAFUJI] I'm getting
nervous waiting for Handa.

485
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:18,791
[STUDENTS]
♪ La, la, la, la...! ♪

486
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:21,625
[AIZAWA] You're not the only
ones with family problems!

487
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:24,708
[KASUMI] Suddenly, King Lear
hobbled onto the dance floor.

488
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:26,541
But was it compassion
or jealousy

489
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,250
that drew him to this scene?

490
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:30,166
I just want to be loved!

491
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:32,833
Despite his name,
he isn't leering much.

492
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:35,708
Oh! How can we make
our love succeed

493
00:19:35,791 --> 00:19:37,333
so we don't end up like you?

494
00:19:37,416 --> 00:19:39,666
You cannot make
love do anything.

495
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:42,416
It must find and nurture itself.

496
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,750
Wise words from King Lear.

497
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,291
I'm killing myself.

498
00:19:46,375 --> 00:19:47,833
[KASUMI]
So she says,

499
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:50,041
but she's only pretending to
be dead until Romeo wakes up.

500
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:51,666
For attention, I suppose.

501
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,833
[STUDENT 11F]
Drama queen.

502
00:19:52,916 --> 00:19:56,708
[REO gasps]

503
00:19:56,791 --> 00:19:58,833
Oh, no! My Juliet!

504
00:19:58,916 --> 00:19:59,958
[ACTORS]
Focus on healing!

505
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:01,541
[REO]
But you're too young to die!

506
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:05,125
[ALL] Focus on healing!
Focus on healing!

507
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:07,416
It's back to the bachelor life!

508
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:11,375
[grunting] Here I go!

509
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,375
[ACTORS]
Show no mercy!

510
00:20:13,458 --> 00:20:16,833
Show no mercy!

511
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:20,166
[MIYOKO] You better not put the
mack on Desdemona, you creep!

512
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:22,458
[KASUMI] Then, for some reason,
Othello showed up.

513
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:25,916
When Juliet awoke
all hell broke loose.

514
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,791
King Lear is not having it!

515
00:20:27,875 --> 00:20:29,083
[STUDENTS cheer]

516
00:20:29,166 --> 00:20:30,458
[KASUMI] Shakespeare
crossovers are dangerous.

517
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:33,500
[KAWAFUJI] People like this?
It's all over the place.

518
00:20:33,583 --> 00:20:35,583
Cease your fighting now!

519
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:37,916
These dignified words
echoed across the room

520
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:42,041
and all the unruly fictional
characters went silent.

521
00:20:44,875 --> 00:20:46,416
[KASUMI]
The one who stopped the conflict

522
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:48,750
was none other than
Queen Elizabeth I.

523
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:50,541
For who else could it be?

524
00:20:50,625 --> 00:20:52,625
[STUDENTS cheering]

525
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:54,666
[KASUMI]
Elizabeth was like a mother.

526
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:57,208
And the subjects, her children.

527
00:20:57,291 --> 00:21:01,041
[KAWAFUJI]
What the hell are you doing?

528
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:03,708
[KASUMI] ...for truly did
the people love their queen.

529
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:07,250
[HANDA]
What the hell am I doing?

530
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:10,541
I only had one line and the
narrator stole it from me.

531
00:21:10,625 --> 00:21:11,750
What's to cheer about?

532
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,875
I'm just some idiot
sitting in a chair.

533
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:16,333
Also, why is the whole room
acting like they're praying?

534
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:18,333
The audience too!
Everyone except--

535
00:21:18,416 --> 00:21:20,000
[HANDA gasps]

536
00:21:20,083 --> 00:21:22,333
[HANDA]
Kawafuji? Why are you here?

537
00:21:22,416 --> 00:21:24,458
[KAWAFUJI]
Is this... my fault?

538
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:27,875
[HANDA] I can see the pity
in his eyes. I'm sorry.

539
00:21:27,958 --> 00:21:31,416
It must be terrible having a
clown like me as your friend.

540
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:34,875
If you're embarrassed,
I can hardly blame you.

541
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:39,375
I can't take this anymore.
I've gotta get off this stage!

542
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:41,125
But I can't ruin the show.

543
00:21:41,208 --> 00:21:43,500
What would Elizabeth say
at a time like this?

544
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:44,666
[STUDENT 11C gasps]

545
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:45,916
[STUDENT 11D]
The queen is standing up!

546
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,083
[STUDENT 11B]
She's going to say something!

547
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:50,375
I'm off to defeat...
the Spanish Armada.

548
00:21:50,458 --> 00:21:52,250
[STUDENTS gasp]

549
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,208
[STUDENTS cheer]

550
00:21:54,291 --> 00:21:56,375
[GUY 11A] I dunno what that
means. But kick their ass!

551
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:57,500
[STUDENT 11C]
Good luck, your majesty!

552
00:21:57,583 --> 00:21:59,625
[HASEGAWA]
Our future is in your hands!

553
00:21:59,708 --> 00:22:00,875
[TSUTSUI]
Wait for me, my queen!

554
00:22:00,958 --> 00:22:03,416
[AIZAWA]
King Lear, to battle!

555
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,333
It looks like everybody's
fighting the Spanish Armada.

556
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:08,291
I guess that's the end.

557
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:10,291
[HIROE] We'll have another
show this afternoon,

558
00:22:10,375 --> 00:22:11,500
so please come again!

559
00:22:11,583 --> 00:22:12,958
[KAWAFUJI]
Aw, man.

560
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:14,208
[HANDA screams]

561
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:16,000
[KAWAFUJI] I think he's
really upset this time.

562
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:19,291
[STUDNETS]
Handa!

563
00:23:50,541 --> 00:23:52,000
[HASEGAWA] Shoulda known
we couldn't compete

564
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:54,041
with Handa's class.

565
00:23:54,125 --> 00:23:56,083
[KAWAFUJI]
Oh. Uh, yeah...

566
00:23:56,166 --> 00:23:57,625
C'mon, that was a blast!

567
00:23:57,708 --> 00:24:00,583
What's with that totally
bored look on your face?

568
00:24:00,666 --> 00:24:05,166
I'm not bored. I've just
got a lot on my mind.

569
00:24:05,250 --> 00:24:06,375
[SHAVE]
Gotta hand it to 'em,

570
00:24:06,458 --> 00:24:07,875
this is one hell of
a school festival.

571
00:24:07,958 --> 00:24:09,375
[MOB BOY 11A]
It's Kuro High!

572
00:24:09,458 --> 00:24:10,916
[BROW-BOY] We may as well
enjoy this while we're at it.

573
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,125
Let's pay our respects
to Handa, shall we?

574
00:24:14,208 --> 00:24:19,166
[ALL chuckle]

